class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> nextGreaterElements(vector<int>& nums) {
        int n = nums.size();
        vector<int> ans(n,-1);
        stack<int> st;
        for(int i = 0; i< 2*n;i++){
            while(!st.empty() && nums[st.top()] < nums[i % n]){
                ans[st.top()] = nums[i % n];
                st.pop();
            }
            if (i < n)
            st.push(i);
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
Create an answer array ans of size n initialized with -1.
Use a monotonic decreasing stack to store indices of elements whose next greater element has not been found yet.
Since the array is circular, traverse it twice (0 to 2*n - 1).
For each index i, access the current element using nums[i % n].
While the stack is not empty and the current element is greater than the element at the index on the top of the stack:
Set the current element as the next greater element for that index.
Pop the index from the stack.
Push indices into the stack only during the first traversal (i < n).
After completing the traversal, any indices left in the stack do not have a greater element, so their answer remains -1.
